WEBVTT

00:00.001 --> 00:02.185
<i>Previously on
"The Night Shift"...</i>

00:02.186 --> 00:04.370
I got the rejection letter
from Loyola earlier.

00:04.372 --> 00:05.855
Now this one from Seton Hall.

00:05.856 --> 00:07.339
That's five law-school
rejections. Game over.

00:07.341 --> 00:09.108
We started moving it,
then we saw her neck

00:09.110 --> 00:10.342
hanging by a thread...
Literally.

00:10.344 --> 00:13.545
- Where is she?
- Right here.

00:13.547 --> 00:14.680
What's going on?

00:14.682 --> 00:16.582
Your wife was in an accident,

00:16.583 --> 00:18.483
and your son may still
be at the crash site.

00:18.486 --> 00:20.519
[Loud explosion]
<i>What was that?</i>

00:20.521 --> 00:22.621
- Major, we have casualties.
- I gotta go.

00:22.623 --> 00:24.423
- 24.
<i>- 7.</i>

00:24.425 --> 00:25.424
I love you.

00:25.426 --> 00:26.692
Sharbat, you're pregnant.

00:26.694 --> 00:27.626
Do you have a husband?

00:27.628 --> 00:29.094
Give me my wife!

00:29.096 --> 00:30.229
Listen, I'm sick of your...

00:30.231 --> 00:31.330
Give her to me.

00:32.400 --> 00:33.732
Syd: Drew!
[ Gunshot ]

00:34.735 --> 00:36.268
Drew!

00:37.405 --> 00:39.371
[ Echoing ] Drew!

00:39.373 --> 00:40.572
Drew!

00:42.376 --> 00:43.542
Drew!

00:45.046 --> 00:46.345
Are you okay?

00:46.347 --> 00:48.547
Ohh. I'm shot!
I'm shot!

00:48.549 --> 00:50.215
GSW to the left shoulder!

00:50.217 --> 00:51.350
Are <i> you</i> okay?

00:51.352 --> 00:53.385
Yeah, yeah, the gun just
went off, Syd.

00:53.387 --> 00:55.504
- Here.
- I shot him.

00:55.505 --> 00:57.622
He shot me!
Arrest him! He shot me!

00:57.625 --> 00:59.558
Yeah, and now he's gonna
fix you up now

00:59.560 --> 01:01.493
so I can save your wife
and baby.

01:01.495 --> 01:03.429
You check him out.
If his vitals are stable,

01:03.431 --> 01:04.797
you get him straight to C.T.!

01:04.799 --> 01:06.665
[ Akmal speaks indistinctly ]

01:06.667 --> 01:08.667
Can you at least do that?

01:11.338 --> 01:14.640
I need someone to clean up
this blood, stat!

01:14.642 --> 01:17.509
Okay, where were we?

01:21.582 --> 01:23.849
Okay, let's go, come on!

01:23.851 --> 01:25.717
The pilot says the wind's
gusting too much.

01:25.719 --> 01:26.718
It's not safe to fly.

01:26.720 --> 01:27.753
Come on, Frankie.

01:27.755 --> 01:30.622
- He looks cyanotic.
- Yeah.

01:30.624 --> 01:32.257
Come on, little buddy.

01:32.259 --> 01:34.193
His abdomen's rigid.
He's bleeding internally.

01:34.195 --> 01:36.328
We need to warm him up now
or his blood won't clot.

01:36.330 --> 01:38.597
I can warm him from the inside.

01:38.598 --> 01:40.865
Frankie, honey, this is gonna
sting a little bit.

01:42.369 --> 01:44.169
- [ Groans ]
- It's okay, Frankie,

01:44.171 --> 01:45.437
we're gonna take care of you.

01:45.439 --> 01:47.873
Scalpel.
Yep.

01:49.443 --> 01:52.511
All right, sweetie, here we go.

01:57.184 --> 01:59.284
- Chest tube.
- Yep.

02:00.221 --> 02:03.455
Come on.

02:03.457 --> 02:05.557
I'm in!
Okay.

02:05.559 --> 02:06.758
Saline.

02:06.760 --> 02:08.560
Man:
<i>5631, clear for takeoff.</i>

02:08.562 --> 02:10.229
All right, we've been cleared
for takeoff.

02:10.231 --> 02:11.897
He's waking up.
Good job, Jordan.

02:11.899 --> 02:14.466
Thanks. You too.

02:15.870 --> 02:17.603
You okay?

02:17.605 --> 02:19.872
Yeah. You?

02:19.874 --> 02:22.608
Yeah.

02:25.813 --> 02:28.480
I'm gonna be swamped, so I need
you covering the E.R. for me,

02:28.482 --> 02:31.650
and remember, you represent the
surgical department down there, so...

02:31.652 --> 02:33.118
No reindeer games, I got it.

02:33.119 --> 02:34.585
Yeah, and don't fight
with that girl, Shannon.

02:34.588 --> 02:35.854
She'll kill you.

02:35.856 --> 02:37.356
How's Joan doing?

02:37.358 --> 02:38.590
She was oxygenating a while,

02:38.592 --> 02:39.908
so I took her off the vent.

02:39.909 --> 02:41.225
Still seems a bit
confused, though.

02:41.228 --> 02:42.728
She's acting nervous.

02:42.729 --> 02:44.229
Asking a lot of questions
about Frankie.

02:44.231 --> 02:45.664
She's worried about her son.

02:45.666 --> 02:47.533
I think I can help with that.

02:47.535 --> 02:49.801
Joan, Francis.

02:49.803 --> 02:52.371
I've got some good news.
They found your boy.

02:52.373 --> 02:53.438
- Frankie?!
- He's coming in now on medevac.

02:53.440 --> 02:54.673
- He's here?
- Thank god, is he okay?

02:54.675 --> 02:56.108
- How is he?
- You're tearing your sutures!

02:56.109 --> 02:57.542
Joan, you should relax.
Push morphine, please.

02:57.545 --> 02:59.478
- What is happening?
- She tore her sutures.

02:59.480 --> 03:01.613
We gotta get her to the O.R.
before she bleeds out.

03:01.615 --> 03:02.814
Dr. Zia will fill you in
on your son.

03:02.816 --> 03:04.183
Let's go, let's go!

03:04.185 --> 03:05.717
[ Crying ]

03:08.355 --> 03:11.356
Yes, Akmal's vitals are stable.

03:11.358 --> 03:13.325
Yes, sir. We're waiting
on the C.T. results

03:13.327 --> 03:15.444
to determine the location
of the bullet.

03:15.445 --> 03:17.562
Gen. Rozenfeld: But I told you to
get them off the base, and I meant it!

03:17.565 --> 03:19.298
This is the last we're
discussing the matter!

03:19.300 --> 03:21.533
Yes, sir.
Yes, I will handle it.

03:21.535 --> 03:23.769
I will.
I will handle it.

03:23.771 --> 03:26.238
[ Sighs ]

03:26.240 --> 03:27.740
We are so screwed.

03:27.741 --> 03:29.241
It was bad enough you lied
to the general.

03:29.243 --> 03:30.642
He brought a gun
into the O.R.

03:30.644 --> 03:32.311
What did you want me to do?

03:32.313 --> 03:34.646
Let the mps handle it.
You know how this looks, drew?

03:34.648 --> 03:36.782
You didn't want Sharbat to go.
That's on record.

03:36.784 --> 03:38.684
Now you're involved
with Akmal's shooting?

03:38.686 --> 03:40.485
You could be facing
an article 15.

03:40.487 --> 03:41.987
It was self-defense.

03:41.988 --> 03:43.488
You want me to wait for backup
to get there?

03:43.490 --> 03:44.690
Akmal could have killed us all.

03:44.692 --> 03:45.857
You do realize that, right?

03:45.859 --> 03:47.526
You have nine days left, major.

03:47.528 --> 03:49.661
You want your daughter to be
motherless because...

03:49.663 --> 03:51.263
Don't ever, ever say that.

03:51.265 --> 03:52.497
I'm just pointing out
the fact...

03:52.499 --> 03:53.665
This is over.
This is the army, drew.

03:53.667 --> 03:55.559
This is not a democracy.

03:55.560 --> 03:57.452
We have orders to follow,
and follow them, we will.

03:57.453 --> 03:59.345
Okay, so just to hell with
the Hippocratic oath, then.

03:59.346 --> 04:01.238
Just throw that out the window.
So here's how it's gonna happen, all right?

04:01.242 --> 04:03.408
When Sharbat and Akmal
are stable, they leave.

04:03.410 --> 04:05.677
We do not interfere
with local medical decisions.

04:05.679 --> 04:07.546
That comes straight
from the Pentagon.

04:07.548 --> 04:11.250
- Okay, if I may...
- No, you may <i> not,</i> captain.

04:11.252 --> 04:13.685
I have given a year of my life
to this dump,

04:13.687 --> 04:16.588
and in 14 days, my daughter,
Riley, turns 13,

04:16.589 --> 04:17.889
and I am going home.

04:17.891 --> 04:19.591
I am not missing that

04:19.591 --> 04:21.291
because you forgot
the chain of command.

04:21.295 --> 04:22.694
Are we clear?

04:22.696 --> 04:24.696
Yes, ma'am.

04:24.698 --> 04:25.797
Sorry, ma'am.

04:27.000 --> 04:33.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

04:48.022 --> 04:49.955
Jordan, you want to take
Frankie up?

04:49.957 --> 04:52.424
No, go on up.
I'll stay on the floor.

04:52.426 --> 04:54.026
We got Frankie's temp up.

04:54.027 --> 04:55.627
He's in hypoglemic shock,
injury to the bowel,

04:55.629 --> 04:57.029
filled the belly with blood.

04:57.031 --> 04:58.664
We got to open him up
to stop the bleeding.

04:58.666 --> 04:59.965
Hang o-neg,
put him on the cell saver.

04:59.967 --> 05:01.600
- I'm scrubbing in.
- All right, doctor.

05:01.602 --> 05:03.468
Paul's closing on Frankie's mom
right now.

05:03.470 --> 05:05.037
Wha... I thought she was
out of surgery.

05:05.039 --> 05:07.072
She was despondent post-op,
ripped her sutures.

05:07.074 --> 05:08.774
We ran her back in.
[ Sighs ]

05:08.776 --> 05:10.442
I was only with her
two hours ago.

05:10.444 --> 05:12.444
If I'd seen her maybe
in the recovery room.

05:12.446 --> 05:13.912
Hey, hey,
you saved a dying woman.

05:13.914 --> 05:15.981
You can't be in two places
at one time.

05:15.983 --> 05:19.551
Yeah, yeah,
try telling <i> him</i> that.

05:23.457 --> 05:25.357
If it's bad news, keep walking.
We got lucky.

05:25.359 --> 05:27.426
Akmal just had a through
and through in the shoulder.

05:27.428 --> 05:28.994
I repaired it
and sent him to recovery.

05:28.996 --> 05:31.463
- Hmm.
- How's Sharbat?

05:31.465 --> 05:34.499
Critical, but her cardiac
output is good.

05:34.501 --> 05:36.101
Her family sold her
to that dirtbag

05:36.103 --> 05:37.753
when she was just 13, major.

05:37.754 --> 05:39.404
Man: Whoa, whoa, hold on!
You can't go in there.

05:39.406 --> 05:41.023
Your sister's in surgery.

05:41.024 --> 05:42.641
Sounds like Sharbat's brother
finally tracked her down.

05:42.643 --> 05:44.376
Son of a bitch. Now her
drug-dealing brother's here?

05:44.378 --> 05:45.611
She asked to see him, drew.

05:45.612 --> 05:46.845
I don't care.
He's not coming in here.

05:46.847 --> 05:50.082
Marquez,
have the mps bring him in.

05:50.084 --> 05:52.951
Make sure he's been patted down.

05:52.953 --> 05:56.355
Okay, bring him in, sergeant.

06:02.896 --> 06:05.130
My name is Omed Gilzhai.

06:05.132 --> 06:07.566
I demand to see my sister!

06:07.568 --> 06:11.036
Scary drug dealer, huh?
How do you feel now?

06:11.038 --> 06:12.704
Don't even.

06:12.706 --> 06:15.841
Badass save out there, doc.
We got lucky.

06:15.843 --> 06:18.009
So, any chance you reconsidered
what I asked?

06:18.011 --> 06:19.711
Still not a good time, Sam.

06:19.713 --> 06:21.947
"It's not you, it's me."
Got it.

06:21.949 --> 06:24.049
After three times, quit asking.

06:24.051 --> 06:26.518
<i>Satellite pharmacy,
pick up extension 23.</i>

06:26.520 --> 06:28.820
You just went Dr. no
on that hot fireman?

06:28.822 --> 06:30.822
What?
Your nickname at the clinic.

06:30.824 --> 06:32.824
After all the dudes
you shot down.

06:32.826 --> 06:34.526
[ Chuckles ]
Who are you, Dr. yes?

06:34.528 --> 06:36.595
With him?
Dr. hell yes.

06:36.597 --> 06:38.797
Oh, man, Shannon,
do not date guys from work.

06:38.799 --> 06:40.165
It's not worth it, trust me.

06:40.167 --> 06:42.434
Yeah.
T.C. And Dr. Clemmens.

06:42.436 --> 06:44.102
[ Chuckles ] That must
have been interesting.

06:44.104 --> 06:46.138
Shut it.
Sorry, filter malfunction.

06:46.140 --> 06:48.140
- Yeah.
- Just got a new case.

06:48.142 --> 06:50.175
Frat brother doing
a "jackass" gag.

06:50.177 --> 06:51.676
Wrestled in a ring
of thumb tacks.

06:51.678 --> 06:53.078
- Ow!
- Relax.

06:53.080 --> 06:54.997
I'm working him up,

06:54.998 --> 06:56.915
but I need you to sign off
on my discharge first.

06:56.917 --> 06:59.084
Ranchero with a cold
wants to go.

06:59.086 --> 07:00.652
Reminds me of my grandpa.

07:00.654 --> 07:02.821
He used to run cattle
on the res.

07:02.823 --> 07:04.055
Presenting symptoms?

07:04.057 --> 07:05.891
Weakness, chills, sounded viral.

07:05.893 --> 07:07.959
Told him to go home
and sleep it off.

07:07.961 --> 07:10.862
Okay.
[ Speaking Spanish ]

07:10.864 --> 07:12.197
Gracias.

07:12.199 --> 07:13.899
Okay, you missed something.

07:13.901 --> 07:15.167
Positive belt buckle sign.

07:15.169 --> 07:16.835
You're joking, right?

07:16.836 --> 07:18.502
No. Stoic Hispanic men like him
only see a doctor

07:18.505 --> 07:20.439
if there is something
massively wrong.

07:20.441 --> 07:21.940
But his exam is normal.

07:21.942 --> 07:24.609
Did <i> your</i> grandfather
go to the hospital?

07:24.611 --> 07:26.645
Only if he thought he was dying.

07:26.647 --> 07:29.448
[ Clicks teeth ]
I'll see you in curtain 1.

07:29.450 --> 07:31.750
- Yo, Toph.
- Yeah.

07:31.752 --> 07:33.084
Yeah, so I was thinking,
all right,

07:33.086 --> 07:34.586
about you getting back
out there.

07:34.588 --> 07:35.854
I don't have time for your gym.

07:35.856 --> 07:37.522
- No, no, you don't have to.
- It's good to go.

07:37.524 --> 07:39.891
See, we can do it here.

07:39.893 --> 07:42.127
- I'll be your life coach.
- [ Laughs ]

07:42.129 --> 07:43.512
That's a good one.

07:43.513 --> 07:44.896
[ Scoffs ]
Okay, fine, I tried.

07:44.898 --> 07:47.165
It's your life.
Whatever's left of it.

07:47.167 --> 07:49.134
Here's the labs you requested
for the little boy in the O.R.

07:49.136 --> 07:50.969
Thanks.
Hey, Kenny!

07:50.971 --> 07:53.972
Kenny. Look, I'm sorry
I snapped at you.

07:53.974 --> 07:56.141
If we were to do this... I do
mean "if"... how would it work?

07:56.143 --> 07:58.176
Well, for starters,
we change your bad habits.

07:58.178 --> 07:59.778
Stand while you chart.
Hit the stairs.

07:59.780 --> 08:01.213
I mean, have you ever heard
of an apple?

08:01.215 --> 08:03.515
That's like your third bag
of chips in the last hour.

08:03.517 --> 08:05.684
Look, I do want to get out
and do more badass field stuff,

08:05.686 --> 08:08.253
but more than that, I just don't
want to be the old dad at soccer

08:08.255 --> 08:09.254
who can't play with his kid.

08:09.256 --> 08:10.722
As long as that gets me there.

08:10.724 --> 08:12.023
Oh, absolutely.

08:12.025 --> 08:13.525
I mean, you won't
look like this,

08:13.527 --> 08:14.893
but you won't look like that.

08:14.895 --> 08:16.761
Okay, coach.
Yeah?

08:16.763 --> 08:19.164
All right, let me track
your heart rate,

08:19.166 --> 08:22.100
calories burned,
and steps for my phone.

08:22.102 --> 08:24.035
I use it with all my clients.

08:24.037 --> 08:25.670
A little creepy, but okay.

08:25.672 --> 08:26.905
I'm gonna see the kid.

08:26.907 --> 08:28.640
Surgery's on the third floor.

08:28.642 --> 08:29.875
Yeah, I know.

08:29.877 --> 08:32.244
Oh! Hit the stairs?

08:32.246 --> 08:33.745
Great idea.

08:33.746 --> 08:36.715
There we go.
Oh, after you.

08:36.717 --> 08:38.817
So, Frankie injured his small
bowel when he was thrown.

08:38.818 --> 08:40.818
Our surgeon's removing
the damaged tissue now, so...

08:40.821 --> 08:41.919
We adopted Frankie.

08:41.922 --> 08:43.054
Yeah.

08:43.056 --> 08:45.157
We couldn't get pregnant.

08:45.158 --> 08:47.259
We got him, and...
He's part of us now.

08:47.261 --> 08:49.160
If we lost him, Joan will never
forgive herself.

08:49.162 --> 08:50.529
She grew up pentecostal.

08:50.530 --> 08:51.897
She thinks this is god
punishing her.

08:51.899 --> 08:54.799
I know how hard this is,

08:54.801 --> 08:57.202
but he's gonna make it.

08:57.204 --> 08:58.770
I promise.

08:58.772 --> 09:00.205
Do me a favor, doc.

09:00.206 --> 09:01.639
If you have bad news,
you tell me, not Joan.

09:01.642 --> 09:03.208
She can get a little hysterical.

09:03.210 --> 09:05.544
Yeah, of course, Francis.
You excuse me?

09:05.546 --> 09:06.278
Okay.

09:06.280 --> 09:07.979
- Hey.
- Hey.

09:07.981 --> 09:09.631
I just got Frankie's labs.

09:09.632 --> 09:11.282
His platelets and white
blood cells are way down.

09:11.285 --> 09:12.951
- Does Scott know?
- It's doubtful.

09:12.953 --> 09:14.686
He's too busy putting
him back together.

09:14.688 --> 09:16.204
All right.

09:16.205 --> 09:17.721
I just told Frankie's dad
he was gonna make it.

09:17.724 --> 09:19.708
Why'd you do that?

09:19.709 --> 09:21.693
I don't know.
It just kind of came out.

09:21.695 --> 09:24.629
I guess I'd better
go help Scott.

09:29.336 --> 09:31.870
All right, Mr. Martinez,
this might just be the flu,

09:31.872 --> 09:34.172
but we want to make sure
it's nothing more serious,

09:34.174 --> 09:35.740
so we're gonna run
a few more tests.

09:35.742 --> 09:37.742
No tests, I just have a susto.

09:37.744 --> 09:40.211
A "fright illness"?

09:40.213 --> 09:41.947
Okay.

09:41.949 --> 09:44.349
[ Speaking Spanish ]

09:44.351 --> 09:46.084
I'm not scared of nothing.

09:46.086 --> 09:48.253
Okay, well,
I like your bracelets.

09:48.255 --> 09:50.622
Are they helping
with your arthritis?

09:50.624 --> 09:52.724
Sí.
My curandera gave them to me.

09:52.726 --> 09:54.292
Your healer?

09:54.294 --> 09:57.128
All right, well, did she give
you anything for your susto?

09:59.733 --> 10:01.132
Well, I don't get it.

10:01.134 --> 10:03.835
I mean, if you have a cure,
why are you here?

10:03.837 --> 10:07.005
My patron won't let me work
without a doctor's note.

10:07.007 --> 10:08.340
I break horses.

10:08.342 --> 10:11.009
My gramps did that.
He put them on a long rope,

10:11.011 --> 10:13.144
let them run, then bring it in
a little at a time.

10:13.146 --> 10:15.380
They're like people.
They hate being told what to do.

10:15.382 --> 10:18.650
I like this girl.
She's smart.

10:19.252 --> 10:20.285
All right, I tell you what.

10:20.287 --> 10:21.620
Why don't you let us do our jobs

10:21.622 --> 10:22.902
so we can get you back to yours?

10:24.124 --> 10:25.290
Okay.

10:28.161 --> 10:30.328
[ Monitor beeping ]

10:30.330 --> 10:32.631
He beat her
when she was pregnant?

10:32.633 --> 10:34.199
And that's not against the law.

10:34.201 --> 10:35.300
Akmal <i> is</i> the law.

10:35.302 --> 10:37.202
We shamed him
by trying to leave,

10:37.204 --> 10:39.304
and after the baby comes,
he will kill us both,

10:39.306 --> 10:41.072
unless I can get us
to Australia.

10:41.074 --> 10:43.041
It's the stone ages, I get it,
but our hands are tied.

10:43.043 --> 10:44.342
[ Monitor beeps rapidly ]

10:44.344 --> 10:47.412
The baby's having recurrent
decelerations.

10:52.152 --> 10:55.286
Damn.
The uterine lac is extended.

10:55.288 --> 10:56.821
My baby?

10:56.823 --> 10:58.390
How's my baby?

10:58.392 --> 10:59.924
Everyone is fine.

10:59.926 --> 11:01.426
You have a visitor.

11:01.428 --> 11:04.396
Omed?
You didn't go?

11:04.398 --> 11:06.131
Without you, never.

11:08.135 --> 11:11.002
The uterine lac
is rapidly expanding.

11:11.004 --> 11:12.370
How many c-sections
have you done?

11:12.372 --> 11:13.905
Two.

11:13.907 --> 11:16.374
Great, that's one more than me,
you're hired.

11:21.214 --> 11:23.331
How's he doing?

11:23.332 --> 11:25.449
Removed the injured bowel,
but he's oozing everywhere.

11:25.452 --> 11:27.385
'Cause he has no platelets.
He needs them to clot.

11:27.387 --> 11:29.254
- These should help.
- Temp's up to 104.

11:29.256 --> 11:30.755
He went from freezing
to burning up.

11:30.757 --> 11:32.290
His white blood cell count
is down, too.

11:32.292 --> 11:33.925
You thinking what I'm thinking?

11:33.927 --> 11:35.427
Traumatic bone marrow failure.

11:35.429 --> 11:37.796
Without working bone marrow,
he can't make new blood cells,

11:37.798 --> 11:39.698
which means he can't clot
or fight infection.

11:39.700 --> 11:41.933
He needs a transplant.
Go test the parents for a match.

11:41.935 --> 11:43.468
Won't help, he's adopted.

11:43.470 --> 11:45.303
Well, then, try and track down
his birth mother.

11:45.305 --> 11:47.022
That's his best shot.

11:47.023 --> 11:48.740
We can start him on antibiotics
and slow the infection,

11:48.742 --> 11:49.874
but without a transplant.

11:49.876 --> 11:51.776
All right, I'm on it.

11:51.778 --> 11:53.845
Find me a match,
or he's not gonna make it!

12:00.887 --> 12:02.921
Now, you sure you don't want us
to put you under?

12:02.923 --> 12:05.423
You could wake up, and your son
would be right here.

12:05.425 --> 12:06.891
No, not with Akmal around.

12:06.893 --> 12:08.793
I have to be awake
to protect my son.

12:08.795 --> 12:10.729
I would do the same thing.

12:10.731 --> 12:12.230
You have kids, doctor?

12:12.232 --> 12:14.999
I do. I have a daughter
named Riley in Texas.

12:15.001 --> 12:16.935
She's gonna be 13 in two weeks.

12:16.937 --> 12:19.237
- I married Akmal at 13.
- Yeah?

12:19.239 --> 12:21.973
Riley's gonna have a slumber
party for her birthday.

12:21.975 --> 12:24.042
It's gonna be no boys allowed.

12:24.044 --> 12:25.910
Drew: Your daughter's lucky to
have such a strong role model.

12:25.912 --> 12:27.879
The army's tough on women,
especially moms.

12:27.881 --> 12:29.981
Yeah, well, if you don't push
for change, it never happens.

12:29.983 --> 12:31.916
- You got that right.
- It still sucks.

12:31.918 --> 12:34.285
My ex has this girly
girlfriend, Lexi.

12:34.287 --> 12:37.222
She got fake nails, hair,
boobs, the whole thing.

12:37.224 --> 12:39.023
She wants Riley to do
beauty pageants.

12:39.025 --> 12:40.492
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]
Aah.

12:40.494 --> 12:42.994
- Baby wants out.
- Is he okay?

12:42.996 --> 12:45.263
He's gonna be fine. We have
to start the surgery now.

12:45.265 --> 12:48.800
So I want you to breathe
like I showed you.

12:48.802 --> 12:50.001
In through the nose...

12:50.003 --> 12:51.803
Out through your mouth.

12:51.805 --> 12:53.004
Starting low transverse
incision.

12:53.006 --> 12:54.906
Through the nose,
out through the mouth.

12:54.908 --> 12:56.141
Aah!

12:56.143 --> 12:58.443
Tell me more about her...
Riley.

12:58.445 --> 13:02.180
Well, she's... she's tall,
like her daddy,

13:02.182 --> 13:05.049
and she can beat up any boy
in her class.

13:05.051 --> 13:06.518
I guess she gets that from me.

13:06.520 --> 13:09.087
We got this, Sharbat.

13:10.957 --> 13:13.124
Hey, Topher. You called
for a surgical consult?

13:13.126 --> 13:14.626
I did. Where's Scott?

13:14.627 --> 13:16.127
In surgery.
I'm covering the E.R. for him.

13:16.129 --> 13:17.796
That's all right.
I'm good.

13:17.798 --> 13:20.899
I had a bowel obstruction
I wanted a consult on.

13:20.901 --> 13:23.401
I was 99% sure it wasn't acutely
surgical, so I sent him up.

13:23.403 --> 13:25.136
Oh.

13:25.138 --> 13:27.272
Okay. Uh...

13:27.274 --> 13:29.374
If you... you change
your mind, then.

13:29.376 --> 13:30.376
Hey!

13:31.244 --> 13:34.245
I'm... I'm sorry.

13:34.247 --> 13:37.215
It's hard to headline
in your hometown.

13:37.217 --> 13:39.050
I'm from Philly.

13:39.052 --> 13:40.919
No, it's an expression.

13:40.921 --> 13:42.821
You started as an intern,

13:42.823 --> 13:46.090
so everybody sees you
as their little brother.

13:46.092 --> 13:49.027
You want to be taken seriously,
present with authority.

13:49.029 --> 13:51.296
You are a surgeon.
Own it.

13:51.298 --> 13:53.097
Copy.

13:55.068 --> 13:58.002
His sodium levels are good,
which rules out hypernatremia.

13:58.004 --> 13:59.270
Did you check his herbs?

13:59.272 --> 14:01.272
Rosemary and basil, all benign.

14:01.274 --> 14:03.241
Excuse me.

14:03.243 --> 14:04.876
I'm looking for
Augusto Martinez.

14:04.878 --> 14:06.511
- I'm his daughter, Carly.
- One moment, please.

14:06.513 --> 14:08.046
- Thank you.
- Here.

14:08.048 --> 14:09.380
Uh, excuse me, miss Martinez?

14:09.382 --> 14:10.949
- Yes.
- I'm Dr. Alexander.

14:10.951 --> 14:12.951
This is Dr. Rivera.
We're helping your dad.

14:12.953 --> 14:14.185
Is he okay?
I was in my office.

14:14.187 --> 14:15.086
I didn't get the message.

14:15.088 --> 14:16.287
At 1:00 A.M.?

14:16.289 --> 14:17.856
I'm in the middle of a big case.

14:17.858 --> 14:19.858
He's lethargic, claims

14:19.860 --> 14:21.960
that his spirit was frightened
from his body.

14:21.962 --> 14:23.461
[ Scoffs ]
That stupid witch doctor.

14:23.463 --> 14:25.196
Well, did anything happen
to him recently?

14:25.198 --> 14:26.264
Was he in an accident?

14:26.266 --> 14:27.632
[ Phone rings ]
Not that I know of.

14:27.634 --> 14:29.251
I'm sorry.
It's my client.

14:29.252 --> 14:30.869
We're in court in the morning.
I'll find you.

14:30.871 --> 14:32.070
Hey, Greg, we're filing for...

14:32.072 --> 14:33.371
- Jordan.
- Yeah.

14:33.373 --> 14:35.206
Mr. Martinez' BP is dropping
in curtain 1.

14:35.208 --> 14:36.208
He just passed out.

14:42.449 --> 14:44.282
Hey.

14:44.284 --> 14:45.984
How's she doing?

14:45.986 --> 14:47.418
Still sleepy.
Yeah.

14:47.420 --> 14:50.221
- How's my son?
- He has an infection in his blood.

14:50.223 --> 14:52.056
We're keeping it in check
with antibiotics,

14:52.058 --> 14:53.625
but his bone marrow
has gone into failure.

14:53.627 --> 14:56.094
He can't make white cells
to fight the infection.

14:56.096 --> 14:57.996
He's gonna need a transplant.

14:57.998 --> 14:59.497
Transplant?
Yeah.

14:59.499 --> 15:03.067
We need to find
his birth mother.

15:03.069 --> 15:04.269
You still in contact with her?

15:06.072 --> 15:07.105
Francis?

15:07.107 --> 15:08.306
She was a drug addict.

15:08.308 --> 15:10.675
It was a closed adoption.
We never met.

15:10.677 --> 15:12.277
Test me, maybe I'm a match.

15:12.279 --> 15:14.612
Yeah, the chances of a random
match are very slim.

15:14.614 --> 15:18.149
No, please, doc, I want to do
everything I can for my son,

15:18.151 --> 15:19.617
even if it's one in a billion.

15:19.619 --> 15:21.686
Okay.
I'll go tell her.

15:28.261 --> 15:30.995
Okay, Mr. Martinez, your heart
rate and your temperature

15:30.997 --> 15:33.197
are abnormally low,
which is why you passed out.

15:33.199 --> 15:35.166
- What's causing it?
- Hard to say.

15:35.168 --> 15:36.501
So far, his tests
are all normal,

15:36.503 --> 15:38.102
but we'd like to check
a few more things.

15:38.104 --> 15:40.204
No more tests.
I can't afford 'em.

15:40.206 --> 15:41.472
You don't have to, papi.

15:41.474 --> 15:43.007
I don't want your money,
Carolina.

15:43.009 --> 15:44.409
Why not?

15:44.411 --> 15:46.277
Because I'm not cleaning houses
like Ernesto's daughter?

15:46.279 --> 15:48.179
Or selling sugar pills
like your witch doctor?

15:48.181 --> 15:49.580
Okay, everybody,
let's just focus here.

15:49.582 --> 15:51.416
Don't you look down
your nose at me.

15:51.418 --> 15:53.318
Not you, the con artists.

15:53.320 --> 15:54.619
Folk cures are placebos.

15:54.621 --> 15:57.121
Studies show hope helps
patients get well.

15:57.123 --> 15:58.623
[ Laughs ]

15:58.624 --> 16:00.124
The only thing healthy here
is her bank account.

16:00.126 --> 16:01.259
She's robbed him blind.

16:01.261 --> 16:02.427
At least she listens to him.

16:02.428 --> 16:03.594
You didn't even know
he was sick.

16:03.596 --> 16:05.964
- Excuse me?
- Okay.

16:05.966 --> 16:08.533
Uh, Dr. Rivera,
a word outside?

16:14.507 --> 16:16.174
Oh!

16:16.176 --> 16:18.176
Hey, Kenny,
I didn't, uh, see you.

16:18.178 --> 16:19.243
- Dude.
- What?

16:19.245 --> 16:21.312
This thing has 50 grams
of sugar.

16:21.314 --> 16:25.049
Okay, look.
It has 1% daily riboflavin.

16:25.051 --> 16:27.051
[ Laughs ]
It's basically medicine.

16:27.053 --> 16:28.453
How did you find me, anyway?

16:28.455 --> 16:29.687
Ta-da!

16:29.689 --> 16:31.022
You know, this tracker,

16:31.023 --> 16:32.356
you'd make a really good
stalker, Kenny.

16:32.359 --> 16:34.225
You should think about
a career change.

16:34.227 --> 16:36.227
Yeah, you should think about
stepping it up, man.

16:36.229 --> 16:37.428
My grandma moves more than you.

16:37.430 --> 16:39.263
She should take it easy, then.

16:41.568 --> 16:43.101
Ray.

16:43.103 --> 16:44.669
Hey. Hey, brother.

16:44.671 --> 16:46.671
Can you do me a favor?

16:46.672 --> 16:48.672
When you're moving patients
around, can you wear this?

16:48.675 --> 16:50.775
But I already
got one, Dr. Z.

16:50.777 --> 16:52.276
Well, now you have two.

16:52.278 --> 16:55.480
And look, it comes with <i> this.</i>

16:55.482 --> 16:59.250
If anybody asks you,
you didn't get it from me.

16:59.252 --> 17:00.651
Thanks, ray.

17:06.526 --> 17:08.358
So, what the hell was that?

17:08.361 --> 17:11.295
You do not take sides
in a family argument.

17:11.297 --> 17:12.262
Do you hear me?

17:12.265 --> 17:13.664
She's bullying him.

17:13.665 --> 17:15.299
My mom did that to my grandpa.

17:15.300 --> 17:17.101
His voice was like
a dog whistle to her.

17:17.103 --> 17:19.203
Shannon, you cannot bring
emotion into this job.

17:19.204 --> 17:21.204
It clouds your judgment,
and it can hurt your patient.

17:21.207 --> 17:24.075
- So, be a robot.
- Be professional.

17:24.077 --> 17:27.278
I gave you a lot of leeway
at the reservation clinic,

17:27.280 --> 17:28.579
but it is not gonna fly here.

17:28.581 --> 17:30.381
It won't happen again.

17:30.383 --> 17:32.417
Yeah, you're damn straight
it won't.

17:32.419 --> 17:34.585
Annie: Jordan!

17:35.789 --> 17:37.355
Annie.

17:37.357 --> 17:39.223
I heard a rumor
that you were back.

17:39.225 --> 17:41.325
I'm sober, five months now.

17:41.327 --> 17:43.094
Yeah, Tc didn't mention it.

17:43.096 --> 17:45.430
Well, you guys have a lot
of stuff to not...

17:45.432 --> 17:47.265
Talk about besides me.

17:47.267 --> 17:49.333
I'm sorry about everything
that happened with...

17:49.335 --> 17:51.469
Uh-uh,
that's not necessary.

17:51.471 --> 17:56.808
I know, I just... I-i
got to say this, too.

17:56.810 --> 17:58.342
Hi, Topher.

17:58.344 --> 18:00.244
Oh, hey.

18:00.246 --> 18:01.679
You always tried to help me,

18:01.681 --> 18:04.182
and I repaid you by being
a total bitch,

18:04.184 --> 18:07.251
and look...
I'm really sorry.

18:07.253 --> 18:10.421
I-I'm not asking
for forgiveness, Jordan.

18:10.423 --> 18:12.690
I'm just trying not to make
the same mistakes again.

18:12.692 --> 18:14.659
How's that going for you?

18:14.661 --> 18:17.361
It sucks, but in a good way,

18:17.363 --> 18:20.264
so I'm volunteering
at a halfway house.

18:20.266 --> 18:21.833
I'm gonna be here
from time to time.

18:21.835 --> 18:24.302
I'll see ya.

18:24.304 --> 18:25.503
What?

18:25.505 --> 18:27.205
[ Chuckles ]
It's crazy, right?

18:27.207 --> 18:30.675
She showed up one month ago,
gave tee 47 bucks,

18:30.677 --> 18:32.310
determined to pay him back.

18:32.312 --> 18:35.279
I hope it works out, right?
Time will tell.

18:35.281 --> 18:38.282
Wow, I did not see that coming.

18:38.284 --> 18:40.718
Dr. Alexander, my dad,
he won't wake up!

18:41.721 --> 18:44.322
Just fix him!
Do something!

18:44.324 --> 18:46.457
Hey, Toph, I need Frankie's
adoption records asap

18:46.459 --> 18:48.326
so I can contact
his birth mother.

18:48.328 --> 18:50.161
Does your cousin still clerk
for the state?

18:50.163 --> 18:51.896
Yeah, yeah, I'll...
I'll call him right now,

18:51.898 --> 18:53.681
but I gotta be honest, dude.

18:53.682 --> 18:55.465
It's a needle in a haystack
the size of Texas.

18:55.468 --> 18:57.802
Just try, okay?
Okay.

18:59.873 --> 19:01.806
- Oh, my god!
- Gwen?

19:01.808 --> 19:03.241
You okay?

19:03.243 --> 19:04.876
Uh, yeah, yeah.
Have you seen Kenny?

19:04.878 --> 19:06.744
I'm dodging him, actually.

19:06.746 --> 19:08.679
Oh, he ran a patient
up to radiology.

19:08.681 --> 19:10.298
Be back in 10.
[ Radio chatter ]

19:10.299 --> 19:11.916
Copy that, we're on our way.
All right, I gotta jump.

19:11.918 --> 19:13.784
Wait, you want me
to leave him a message?

19:13.786 --> 19:14.919
No, no, I'll catch him
after the shift.

19:14.921 --> 19:15.720
Thanks, Topher.

19:15.722 --> 19:17.388
Happy to help.

19:17.390 --> 19:18.789
[ Baby gurgles ]

19:18.791 --> 19:22.460
He's beautiful, Sharbat.
You did great.

19:22.462 --> 19:25.463
Cutting the umbilical cord.

19:25.465 --> 19:27.331
Here, let's clean him up.

19:27.333 --> 19:28.499
[ Monitor beeps rapidly ]

19:28.501 --> 19:29.917
He's not breathing.

19:29.918 --> 19:31.334
[ Gasps ]
Please help him!

19:31.337 --> 19:33.304
We will.
We just need you to stay calm.

19:33.306 --> 19:33.938
I lost his pulse.

19:33.940 --> 19:36.240
Please, save my baby.

19:36.242 --> 19:37.441
Please help him!

19:37.443 --> 19:39.210
Come on, buddy.
Come on.

19:39.212 --> 19:41.279
Please save my baby.
Please save him.

19:43.950 --> 19:45.149
We need to push epi.
We don't have a line,

19:45.150 --> 19:46.349
so we'll go through
the umbilical cord.

19:46.352 --> 19:47.351
Save my baby!
Please help him!

19:47.353 --> 19:50.188
[ Sobbing ]
Oh, my god.

19:50.190 --> 19:52.323
- Pushing the catheter.
- What's happening?

19:52.325 --> 19:55.726
- Please save him.
- Tie it off, doctor.

19:55.728 --> 19:58.229
Okay, I'm in.
Come on.

19:58.231 --> 20:00.331
Try to stay calm, Sharbat.
We got this.

20:00.333 --> 20:02.466
- Push the epi.
- Epi in.

20:02.468 --> 20:03.501
Here we go.

20:03.503 --> 20:05.436
- Come on, buddy.
- Come on.

20:05.438 --> 20:06.470
Come on.

20:06.472 --> 20:08.406
[ Sobbing continues ]

20:08.408 --> 20:09.373
[ Baby cries ]

20:09.375 --> 20:10.408
There he is.

20:10.410 --> 20:11.709
Good set of lungs on him.

20:11.711 --> 20:13.211
[ Laughs ]

20:13.213 --> 20:14.312
No pneumonia or tumors.

20:14.314 --> 20:16.380
What are all these
bony abnormalities

20:16.382 --> 20:17.448
on the chest X-ray?

20:17.450 --> 20:18.883
Scarring from old fractures.

20:18.885 --> 20:21.385
These guys, they get thrown
off horses, kicked.

20:21.387 --> 20:22.853
I told you, they're tough.

20:22.855 --> 20:24.322
Yeah, they are.
[ Monitor beeps rapidly ]

20:24.324 --> 20:25.690
Okay, his heart rate
keeps dropping.

20:25.692 --> 20:27.725
Let's give him
0.5 of atropine.

20:27.727 --> 20:30.928
It's not doing anything.

20:30.930 --> 20:32.396
All right, let's put him
on pacer pads.

20:32.398 --> 20:34.432
We might need to
pace him externally.

20:34.433 --> 20:36.467
I talked to the chief of
internal medicine at northwest,

20:36.469 --> 20:39.437
and she said that this is
a "beta blocker overdose,"

20:39.439 --> 20:41.439
and he needs glucagon right now.

20:41.441 --> 20:42.907
Okay, that's an
interesting theory,

20:42.909 --> 20:44.475
except he's not
on beta blockers.

20:44.477 --> 20:46.377
Then what's wrong with him?

20:46.379 --> 20:47.929
I don't have an answer.

20:47.930 --> 20:49.480
Well, you better find one
because if you don't,

20:49.482 --> 20:51.382
I'm gonna sue you
and this lousy excuse

20:51.384 --> 20:54.485
for a hospital for malpractice.

20:54.487 --> 20:57.388
Is that how you handle
everything, to bully people?

20:57.390 --> 20:59.357
You know, maybe if you spent
a little less time

20:59.359 --> 21:01.792
on that phone of yours
and more time with him,

21:01.794 --> 21:03.461
he wouldn't be here.

21:06.799 --> 21:08.399
Do as I say, not as I do, right?

21:08.401 --> 21:10.001
Shannon, right now I need smart.

21:10.003 --> 21:11.602
Smart-ass
is a waste of my time.

21:11.604 --> 21:13.537
All right, we've obviously
missed something,

21:13.539 --> 21:15.606
so let's run his labs again.

21:18.344 --> 21:19.944
General Rozenfeld called.

21:19.946 --> 21:23.381
Mark has told him both patients
are in recovery.

21:23.383 --> 21:24.482
I talked to Omed.

21:24.484 --> 21:25.850
They can still make it
to Australia.

21:25.852 --> 21:26.951
No, it's too late.

21:26.953 --> 21:28.719
Akmal's gonna wake up
any minute now.

21:28.721 --> 21:31.355
Actually, I miscalculated
his weight during anesthesia.

21:31.357 --> 21:33.491
I thought he was 220.
Turns out he's 180,

21:33.493 --> 21:35.626
so the post-op morphine
might have been too much.

21:35.628 --> 21:37.862
You dosed him?
On whose orders?

21:37.864 --> 21:39.597
My patient, my call, right?

21:39.599 --> 21:40.698
[ Sighs ]

21:40.700 --> 21:42.433
We can get them back on track,
major.

21:42.435 --> 21:43.734
We can do this.
We've come this far.

21:43.736 --> 21:46.737
Dr. Syd?
You want to hold Umayd?

21:51.744 --> 21:53.544
[ Baby cooing ]

22:03.456 --> 22:06.991
Umayd.
That's a beautiful name.

22:06.993 --> 22:08.993
It means hope.

22:14.067 --> 22:16.567
What did you have in mind?

22:18.438 --> 22:19.437
Dr. Rivera?

22:19.439 --> 22:20.638
Not now, Paul, I'm charting.

22:20.640 --> 22:21.639
It's Dr. Cummings.

22:21.641 --> 22:23.074
[ Scoffs ]
Dr. Cummings.

22:23.076 --> 22:24.608
Somebody put on
his big-boy pants.

22:24.610 --> 22:26.110
Try it some time,
nurse Fournette.

22:26.112 --> 22:27.778
Excuse me.

22:27.780 --> 22:30.381
Darren Cardiff.

22:30.383 --> 22:31.449
Thumb tack man.

22:31.451 --> 22:32.684
I started removing the tacks,

22:32.685 --> 22:33.918
then got pulled
into a critical case,

22:33.920 --> 22:35.486
handed it off to a nurse.

22:35.487 --> 22:37.053
And why did you not call
for a trauma consult?

22:37.056 --> 22:38.389
The wounds are all shallow.

22:38.391 --> 22:39.690
I'm sealing it
with surgical glue.

22:39.692 --> 22:41.525
On whose authority?
You are an intern.

22:41.527 --> 22:43.627
Did you even check a chest X-ray
for a pneumo, maybe?

22:43.629 --> 22:44.962
Dude didn't want stitches,
doctor,

22:44.964 --> 22:46.764
so I suggested another way.

22:46.766 --> 22:49.133
The E.R. uses consultants
for a reason, Dr. Rivera.

22:49.135 --> 22:50.701
41 puncture wounds is a trauma.

22:50.703 --> 22:52.803
Next time, call me
instead of asking a nurse,

22:52.805 --> 22:55.072
or I will note it
in your resident file.

22:57.076 --> 22:59.543
Frankie's bleeding has stopped,
but his BP is still dropping.

22:59.545 --> 23:01.412
He's in shock.
We need that match.

23:01.414 --> 23:02.880
Any luck finding
the birth mother?

23:02.882 --> 23:04.515
No. Francis said
he didn't know.

23:04.517 --> 23:06.117
He was fuzzy on the whole thing.

23:06.119 --> 23:08.452
Couldn't remember her name
or the adoption agency.

23:08.454 --> 23:10.554
How do you forget
where your kid came from?

23:10.556 --> 23:12.123
My parents could still tell you

23:12.125 --> 23:13.624
the address of
their adoption lawyer.

23:13.626 --> 23:15.760
Well, exactly, so I spoke
to Toph's cousin,

23:15.762 --> 23:18.095
and the state has no adoption
records for Frankie.

23:18.097 --> 23:19.463
He doesn't exist.
That's impossible.

23:19.465 --> 23:20.931
The courts keep records
on everything.

23:20.933 --> 23:22.433
I've seen my own
adoption records.

23:22.435 --> 23:23.701
You know what else is weird?

23:23.702 --> 23:24.968
He made me promise not to talk
to his wife,

23:24.971 --> 23:26.270
didn't want to upset her.

23:26.271 --> 23:27.570
Yeah, well, she completely
freaked out

23:27.573 --> 23:29.106
when we told her that
you had found Frankie,

23:29.108 --> 23:30.141
tore her stitches.

23:30.143 --> 23:31.642
That's a pretty
extreme reaction.

23:31.644 --> 23:33.544
Yeah, it is.
What are you thinking?

23:33.546 --> 23:34.879
This isn't passing
the sniff test?

23:34.881 --> 23:36.447
Something stinks for sure.

23:36.448 --> 23:38.014
My gut's telling me
to keep asking questions.

23:38.017 --> 23:39.150
I'd start with the mother.

23:41.821 --> 23:43.554
[ Monitor beeps steadily ]

23:45.858 --> 23:46.991
Joan?

23:46.993 --> 23:48.959
It's Dr. Callahan.

23:48.961 --> 23:50.761
Frankie needs your help.

23:50.763 --> 23:53.097
Is Frankie going to die?

23:53.099 --> 23:54.832
Well, he's very sick.

23:54.834 --> 23:56.667
He needs a bone marrow
transplant.

23:56.669 --> 23:58.068
We need to find
his birth family.

23:58.070 --> 24:00.571
There's no record
of his adoption anywhere.

24:00.573 --> 24:02.173
Can you tell me why?

24:04.844 --> 24:06.744
I'm so sorry.

24:06.746 --> 24:08.446
Hey.

24:08.448 --> 24:11.816
We all make mistakes.

24:11.818 --> 24:14.618
Usually, it's just
we have to deal with them,

24:14.620 --> 24:17.221
but I don't care what you did
back there.

24:17.223 --> 24:18.956
I just care what you do now.

24:18.958 --> 24:21.959
I'd trade my life for his.

24:21.961 --> 24:25.563
Then tell me
about Frankie, Joan.

24:28.201 --> 24:31.969
I was always meant
to be a mother,

24:31.971 --> 24:35.739
but god wouldn't give me a baby.

24:35.741 --> 24:40.578
And then one day, we were coming
out of the movie theater,

24:40.580 --> 24:44.615
and there was Frankie
in a stroller.

24:44.617 --> 24:47.718
And he smiled at me.

24:47.720 --> 24:55.192
And I just knew, in my
heart, he was mine.

24:56.729 --> 25:01.632
Where did "god" give Frankie
to you, Joan?

25:01.634 --> 25:05.636
In a mall... In Austin.

25:09.609 --> 25:11.675
[ Sobs ]

25:20.686 --> 25:22.553
I mean, I-i thought it was
just Tc being Tc,

25:22.555 --> 25:24.121
but he was right
and he found the truth.

25:25.591 --> 25:27.791
Chicago pd contacted
the birth parents,

25:27.793 --> 25:28.859
Rick and Lisa Moran.

25:28.861 --> 25:29.894
They moved to Chicago last year,

25:29.896 --> 25:31.362
and the son's case went cold.

25:31.363 --> 25:32.829
Well, memories of
their loss everywhere,

25:32.832 --> 25:34.448
who could blame them?

25:34.449 --> 25:36.065
Yeah, they're on a plane
right now from O'Hare.

25:36.068 --> 25:38.836
That's three hours away.
He won't make it that long.

25:38.838 --> 25:41.939
[ Gasps ]
Fetal cord blood.

25:41.941 --> 25:43.574
We were gonna save it, remember?

25:43.576 --> 25:45.309
Maybe Frankie's birth parents
saved his.

25:45.311 --> 25:46.877
They're on a plane right now.
We can't reach 'em.

25:46.879 --> 25:49.179
We don't have to.
There's a cryo bank in Austin

25:49.181 --> 25:51.549
where Frankie was stolen.
I'll call.

25:53.219 --> 25:55.853
Fetal cord blood...
Good call, Jordan.

25:55.855 --> 25:58.022
Yeah, we always said
it would come in handy.

25:58.024 --> 25:58.956
Looks like it did.

25:58.958 --> 26:00.257
Yeah.

26:00.259 --> 26:02.860
I shouldn't have said that.
I'm sorry.

26:02.862 --> 26:04.228
Ah.

26:05.765 --> 26:08.032
I got to check on a patient.
Excuse me.

26:12.171 --> 26:14.738
Miss Martinez,
I owe you an apology.

26:14.740 --> 26:17.107
I had no right to talk to you
like that.

26:17.109 --> 26:20.044
No. You're right.

26:20.046 --> 26:22.313
My dad and I would never talk.

26:22.315 --> 26:23.981
My mom died when I was little.

26:23.983 --> 26:25.683
It was just me and my dad.

26:25.685 --> 26:28.252
He worked so hard so I could
have everything I needed.

26:28.254 --> 26:30.254
And you worked hard
so he could stop.

26:30.256 --> 26:32.856
Made partner, bought a house
in Alamo heights,

26:32.858 --> 26:34.942
asked him to move in,

26:34.943 --> 26:37.027
but he wouldn't give up that
ratty trailer at that ranch.

26:37.029 --> 26:38.362
No matter what I do,

26:38.363 --> 26:39.696
he still cares more about
his horses than me.

26:39.699 --> 26:41.899
I don't think that's true.

26:41.901 --> 26:45.069
[ Sighs ]
I'm a lot like your dad.

26:45.071 --> 26:47.271
You know, I work
so I can avoid things,

26:47.273 --> 26:49.673
feel like I'm in control.

26:49.675 --> 26:52.309
That's why he won't
leave the ranch,

26:52.311 --> 26:55.913
and why you are in the office
until 1:00 A.M.

26:55.915 --> 26:57.014
[ Monitor beeps ]

26:57.016 --> 26:58.015
What's happening?!

26:58.017 --> 26:59.533
His heart rate's in his 30s.

26:59.534 --> 27:01.050
Papi! Be careful
with my papi, please.

27:01.053 --> 27:03.153
We tried pacing him, but we're
not getting much capture.

27:03.155 --> 27:04.955
- What did his labs say?
- I reviewed everything.

27:04.957 --> 27:06.290
Those fractures were
the only abnormality.

27:06.292 --> 27:08.325
[ Beeping continues ]

27:08.327 --> 27:09.727
I got it.

27:09.729 --> 27:12.262
Okay. Uh...

27:12.264 --> 27:14.932
There it is, a healed fracture
of the hyoid bone.

27:14.934 --> 27:16.100
Dr. Rivera.

27:16.102 --> 27:18.068
His throat injury,
plus bradycardia,

27:18.070 --> 27:20.104
plus hypothermia
adds up to hypothyroidism.

27:20.106 --> 27:21.689
He's in a myxedema coma.

27:21.690 --> 27:23.273
Let's give him 500 micrograms
of synthroid IV.

27:23.275 --> 27:25.075
We're gonna jump-start
his thyroid.

27:28.114 --> 27:29.947
[ Flatline ]
Okay, he's lost his pulse.

27:29.949 --> 27:31.115
Let's start CPR.

27:31.117 --> 27:32.983
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

27:35.888 --> 27:38.122
Come on, Mr. Martinez.

27:38.124 --> 27:41.125
Kenny?
Admin papers for trauma 2.

27:41.127 --> 27:42.960
Yeah, great.

27:42.962 --> 27:45.129
Yo, yo,
y-you got the t900.

27:45.131 --> 27:46.130
That thing's banging, right?

27:46.132 --> 27:47.931
I just got it.
[ Scoffs ]

27:47.933 --> 27:49.833
I like my old one better.

27:49.835 --> 27:51.335
You <i> just</i> got it?

27:51.337 --> 27:52.703
Yeah.

27:52.705 --> 27:54.204
From Topher.

27:56.876 --> 27:58.742
Oh! [ Scoffs ]

28:05.117 --> 28:07.317
Tough night.

28:07.319 --> 28:09.687
Mind if I bum one?

28:09.689 --> 28:10.788
[ Siren wails ]

28:10.790 --> 28:12.890
Thank you.

28:12.892 --> 28:14.091
You got a light?

28:14.093 --> 28:16.026
[ Thunder crashes ]
Thanks.

28:16.028 --> 28:18.195
That's nice.

28:18.197 --> 28:20.364
[ Thunder crashes ]

28:21.434 --> 28:23.167
[ Chuckles ]

28:24.770 --> 28:26.970
[ Sighs ]

28:26.972 --> 28:30.040
You know, sneaking sodas,
ray the orderly...

28:30.042 --> 28:31.875
I get it.
We're playing.

28:31.877 --> 28:35.112
But smoking, man?
Come on, man, it's just wrong.

28:35.114 --> 28:36.480
I'm gonna save you
the speech, okay?

28:36.482 --> 28:39.049
I-I made a promise.
I'm just cheating myself.

28:39.051 --> 28:40.951
I got small children, remember?

28:40.953 --> 28:42.386
Oh, so that means
you can act like one?

28:42.388 --> 28:44.455
Please, I don't need
a drill sergeant, okay?

28:44.457 --> 28:46.090
I was a ranger.

28:46.092 --> 28:49.860
I ran 12 miles with
a 60-pound pack in 3 hours.

28:49.862 --> 28:51.261
Where's that guy now?

28:51.263 --> 28:52.730
He's gone!

28:52.732 --> 28:55.099
He's eaten up by long hours,
small children,

28:55.101 --> 28:57.968
a wife who's pissed because
my mom's visiting for a month.

28:57.970 --> 29:00.304
All that will kill me
long before this does.

29:00.306 --> 29:02.206
- Two down.
- All right, we take 24.

29:02.208 --> 29:03.774
- You guys take 17.
- You're a grown man.

29:03.776 --> 29:05.008
If you want to quit, quit.

29:05.010 --> 29:06.443
I don't need you giving me crap.

29:09.081 --> 29:11.181
[ Siren wails ]

29:11.183 --> 29:13.517
That's the kid's
fetal cord blood.

29:13.519 --> 29:15.185
They flew it in from Austin.

29:15.187 --> 29:16.153
Tc found it?

29:16.155 --> 29:17.354
No quit in him.

29:19.158 --> 29:20.791
Enjoy your butt.

29:24.497 --> 29:26.330
<i>Smoke it.
What does he know?</i>

29:36.175 --> 29:38.275
She should be able to walk
in about a week or so.

29:38.277 --> 29:41.044
I need you to give her the
antibiotics three times a day

29:41.046 --> 29:42.179
when you change the dressing.

29:42.181 --> 29:43.113
You remember how?

29:43.115 --> 29:44.448
Yes.

29:44.450 --> 29:46.316
Uh, I am like a doctor now.

29:46.318 --> 29:47.818
Whoa, pump the brakes
there, Omed.

29:47.820 --> 29:49.086
Just... Take care of her.

29:49.088 --> 29:50.888
She needs you now
more than ever.

29:50.890 --> 29:52.356
As-salamu alayki, Sharbat.

29:52.358 --> 29:54.358
Wa'alikum asalaam.
Thank you both.

29:54.360 --> 29:57.427
There you go.

29:57.429 --> 29:59.196
Man: Let's go, boys!
Move it out!

30:05.204 --> 30:07.971
So, they found a safe house
in Kabul?

30:07.973 --> 30:10.507
Then they got to walk across
the Pakistan border,

30:10.509 --> 30:13.277
take a bus to Karachi,
fly to Jakarta,

30:13.279 --> 30:14.378
and sail to Christmas Island.

30:14.380 --> 30:16.580
Wow.
Think they'll make it?

30:16.582 --> 30:19.883
They have a chance.
They didn't before.

30:19.885 --> 30:21.552
What made you change your mind?

30:21.554 --> 30:24.454
[ Chuckles ] Riley.

30:24.456 --> 30:26.557
I thought, what if she were
in trouble like Sharbat?

30:26.559 --> 30:28.192
I would want
someone to help her.

30:28.194 --> 30:31.161
Someone who did it because it
was the right thing to do.

30:35.434 --> 30:37.935
Major. Captain.

30:37.937 --> 30:39.970
General Rozenfeld
wants to see you.

30:39.972 --> 30:41.171
We just got out of surgery.

30:41.173 --> 30:42.406
We need to change and shower.

30:42.408 --> 30:44.208
Sorry, he said now.

30:45.177 --> 30:46.910
Gen. Rozenfeld:
You had strict orders

30:46.912 --> 30:48.278
not to meddle in local
medical matters.

30:48.280 --> 30:50.180
Her husband wanted to take her
to a midwife.

30:50.182 --> 30:52.850
Instead, you performed
a c-section.

30:52.852 --> 30:55.018
Sir, in the captain's defense,
we were doing our job.

30:55.020 --> 30:56.220
That job has changed, major.

30:56.222 --> 30:58.322
You of all people
should know that.

30:58.324 --> 30:59.723
With all due respect, sir,

30:59.724 --> 31:01.123
our partner nearly killed
his wife and baby

31:01.126 --> 31:03.006
simply because he didn't want
to be embarrassed.

31:07.399 --> 31:10.267
Crap.

31:10.269 --> 31:12.502
Look, I know this place
is jacked.

31:12.504 --> 31:14.972
Hell, I even respect
what you did.

31:14.974 --> 31:17.541
But the afghanis want your head
on a stick.

31:17.543 --> 31:18.909
I have no choice.

31:18.911 --> 31:21.311
Captain Alister,
your tour is over.

31:24.216 --> 31:26.483
Sir, I have three months left
on my tour.

31:26.485 --> 31:29.586
You <i> had</i> three months.
You'll be stateside next week.

31:29.588 --> 31:31.188
As for you, major.

31:31.190 --> 31:33.657
With the captain gone,
we're grossly understaffed.

31:33.659 --> 31:37.461
Which means, while he's back
in Texas enjoying barbecue,

31:37.463 --> 31:40.330
your tour is extended
another three months.

31:43.035 --> 31:45.102
Dismissed.

31:55.114 --> 31:57.314
You paged me for a consult.
Oh, right this way.

31:57.316 --> 31:59.149
We have a patient with massive
cranial swelling.

31:59.151 --> 32:00.951
- Cerebral thrombosis.
- Well, we checked that.

32:00.953 --> 32:04.054
This guy's head literally
blew up for no reason.

32:04.924 --> 32:06.223
Can you explain it, doctor?

32:06.225 --> 32:10.227
Because we lowly nurses
sure as hell can't.

32:10.229 --> 32:11.628
Hilarious, Kenny.

32:13.699 --> 32:16.700
[ Laughter ]

32:16.702 --> 32:19.002
Pulse and blood pressure are up.

32:19.004 --> 32:21.171
Thank you.

32:21.173 --> 32:23.373
Dr. Alexander...

32:23.375 --> 32:26.043
And I'm... I'm sorry
I took my issues out on you.

32:26.045 --> 32:28.078
Ah.
Heat of the battle.

32:28.080 --> 32:29.713
[ Chuckles ]

32:33.185 --> 32:35.986
Welcome back, papi.
[ Chuckles ]

32:35.988 --> 32:37.521
Carolina.

32:37.523 --> 32:39.122
You're here.

32:39.124 --> 32:40.991
And so are you.

32:40.993 --> 32:42.092
Thanks to them.

32:42.094 --> 32:44.594
¿Como estas, señor Martinez?

32:44.596 --> 32:47.064
- Tired.
- [ Chuckles ]

32:47.066 --> 32:48.966
But my susta is gone.

32:48.968 --> 32:52.069
Mm. Well, if you want it
to stay that way,

32:52.071 --> 32:53.437
you're gonna need
some strong medicine.

32:53.439 --> 32:56.306
And... You might not like it.

32:56.308 --> 33:00.010
Whatever you say...
Curandera.

33:00.012 --> 33:02.746
Move in with your daughter.

33:02.748 --> 33:04.748
Let her take care of you,

33:04.750 --> 33:07.117
see you eat right,
take your synthroid.

33:07.119 --> 33:08.618
Add years to your life.

33:08.620 --> 33:12.489
'Cause if you don't, your susta
might just come back.

33:14.693 --> 33:16.426
Oh, papi!

33:16.428 --> 33:19.096
You want from Dr. no
to Dr. Phil.

33:19.098 --> 33:20.163
What happened?

33:20.165 --> 33:21.531
Stopped taking my own advice.

33:21.533 --> 33:23.567
Can I do that, too?
No.

33:23.569 --> 33:26.503
In fact, you and I need to chat
about some ground rules.

33:26.505 --> 33:28.138
Over Tequila later.

33:28.140 --> 33:29.740
Oh, okay, well,
I'm down with that.

33:29.742 --> 33:31.308
All right, get out of here,
go do something.

33:31.310 --> 33:32.509
Okay, good.

33:32.511 --> 33:34.177
How long have you been
in Chicago?

33:34.179 --> 33:36.146
Um, we moved last year.

33:36.148 --> 33:38.548
When the case went cold.
I mean, it was so hard to go.

33:38.550 --> 33:40.334
Harder to stay.

33:40.335 --> 33:42.119
I can't imagine what you both
have been through.

33:42.121 --> 33:43.687
But you kept paying to store
the cord blood.

33:43.689 --> 33:45.455
- Good call.
- I mean, we had to.

33:45.457 --> 33:48.125
It was all we had left of him
besides fufu.

33:48.127 --> 33:50.027
[ Monitor beeping ]

33:52.131 --> 33:54.348
It's still very early,

33:54.349 --> 33:56.566
but the transfusion has been
bringing his fever down.

33:59.104 --> 34:00.737
Frankie?

34:00.739 --> 34:04.041
Hey, Frankie.

34:04.043 --> 34:06.343
My name is Dr. Scott.

34:06.345 --> 34:09.679
You were in an accident,
but you're okay now.

34:09.681 --> 34:12.114
I want my mommy.

34:16.121 --> 34:17.587
Fufu?

34:17.589 --> 34:20.724
[ Chuckles ]

34:20.726 --> 34:23.493
He's missed you so much.

34:29.101 --> 34:31.701
I missed you, fufu.

34:33.739 --> 34:35.639
[ Laughing emotionally ]

34:43.348 --> 34:45.114
[ Police radio chatter ]

34:47.152 --> 34:49.119
What about Joan?

34:49.121 --> 34:51.721
She's still in the ICU.

34:51.723 --> 34:53.255
Guess they were so desperate

34:53.257 --> 34:55.324
to have kids
that they stole one.

34:55.327 --> 34:57.394
So twisted, huh?
[ Scoffing ] Yeah.

34:57.396 --> 35:00.230
Hey, how'd that myxedema case
of yours turn out?

35:00.232 --> 35:02.766
Oh, we got him back.
Daughter's not suing.

35:02.768 --> 35:04.451
How did you pull that off?

35:04.452 --> 35:06.135
[ Chuckles ] Well,
she's not a bitch or anything.

35:06.138 --> 35:08.538
She just, you know, was trying
to take control of a situation

35:08.540 --> 35:11.274
that she felt was out
of her hands, which I get.

35:11.276 --> 35:15.212
I spent my whole life trying
to plan every little thing.

35:15.214 --> 35:17.781
Saying no to anything
that I couldn't control,

35:17.783 --> 35:20.183
not letting myself
make any mistakes.

35:20.185 --> 35:23.120
After the baby and everything,
I've been even more like that.

35:23.122 --> 35:25.522
Well, you're just keeping
your eyes on the prize.

35:25.524 --> 35:28.125
What prize... more work?

35:28.127 --> 35:29.626
Feeling like yourself again.

35:29.628 --> 35:31.428
You'll get there.

35:31.430 --> 35:35.198
Well, I know one thing.
I'm done with no.

35:35.200 --> 35:37.134
I want to see where yes gets me.

35:37.136 --> 35:39.870
You know where yes got me.
Aa.

35:39.872 --> 35:41.505
If I leave now,
I can still make a meeting

35:41.507 --> 35:42.873
before all the doughnuts
are gone.

35:42.875 --> 35:44.774
Live and learn,
Dr. Clemmens.

35:44.776 --> 35:46.309
How I roll.

35:46.311 --> 35:49.179
See you tomorrow.
All right.

35:49.181 --> 35:50.413
Yeah.

35:50.415 --> 35:51.648
Long night.

35:51.650 --> 35:53.483
Now I need a drink.

35:53.485 --> 35:55.285
But I can't with Annie around.

35:55.287 --> 35:57.187
Hey, about a run,
blow off some steam?

35:57.189 --> 35:58.755
A run? You?

35:58.757 --> 36:00.857
I don't know. This is new me.
Annie was the old me.

36:00.859 --> 36:02.325
I'm thinking of a 5k this year.

36:02.327 --> 36:04.161
You want to be
my training partner?

36:04.163 --> 36:05.562
You mean kick your butt
in a race?

36:05.564 --> 36:07.197
Those are betting words, pal.

36:07.199 --> 36:09.366
- Yeah.
- We okay, Dr. Cummings?

36:09.368 --> 36:11.668
- You tell me.
- Look, we're family here.

36:11.670 --> 36:13.270
We may mess with you sometimes,

36:13.272 --> 36:14.905
but we'll always have your back.

36:14.907 --> 36:15.939
Just don't be an ass.

36:15.941 --> 36:17.174
Lesson learned.

36:17.176 --> 36:19.176
All right, thanks.
Okay.

36:20.913 --> 36:23.747
[ Scoffs ] Amateur.

36:23.749 --> 36:26.750
Hey, just the man
I was looking for.

36:26.752 --> 36:28.351
I like the sound of that.

36:28.353 --> 36:30.353
I got into Georgetown.
They just e-mailed me.

36:30.355 --> 36:32.289
Somebody dropped out,
I'm off the wait list.

36:32.291 --> 36:34.524
You got into Georgetown?
Yes, I got into Georgetown.

36:34.526 --> 36:36.826
You got into Georgetown!
Yes! That's amazing!

36:36.828 --> 36:38.395
That's amazing!

36:38.397 --> 36:39.863
We're gonna celebrate
all summer.

36:39.865 --> 36:41.298
Where you wanna go?

36:41.300 --> 36:43.366
I got to talk to you about that.

36:43.368 --> 36:45.335
I got to leave tomorrow.

36:45.337 --> 36:47.537
What?

36:47.538 --> 36:49.738
Yeah, I'll... I'll tell you
a little bit more about it

36:49.741 --> 36:51.741
when I get back, okay?

36:51.743 --> 36:53.476
I'm gonna see you on Thursday.

36:53.478 --> 36:54.978
All right.

36:54.980 --> 36:57.280
I'm sorry I won't...
I won't be able

36:57.282 --> 36:59.249
to be there for your birthday.

36:59.251 --> 37:01.251
<i>I didn't think
you'd make it anyway.</i>

37:01.253 --> 37:02.786
<i>It's okay.</i>

37:02.788 --> 37:05.388
Is that...
Is that Riley?

37:05.390 --> 37:08.825
Oh. Honey, this is drew,
who I was telling you about.

37:08.827 --> 37:10.894
Hey.
I just wanted to tell you

37:10.896 --> 37:13.296
that your mom did something
really amazing today.

37:13.298 --> 37:14.631
She was awesome.

37:14.633 --> 37:16.600
You would have been
really proud of her.

37:16.602 --> 37:17.701
I was.

37:17.703 --> 37:19.503
<i>Hey, mom, I gotta go.</i>

37:19.504 --> 37:21.304
<i>Lexi and I are trying on
bridesmaid dresses.</i>

37:21.306 --> 37:24.341
Bridesmaids?
Who's getting married?

37:24.343 --> 37:25.742
<i>Lexi and dad.</i>

37:25.744 --> 37:27.010
What?

37:27.012 --> 37:28.645
<i>They got engaged
a few weeks ago.</i>

37:28.647 --> 37:29.579
<i>He didn't tell you.</i>

37:29.581 --> 37:30.747
Oh!

37:30.749 --> 37:33.850
Oh, right, right.

37:33.852 --> 37:36.753
<i>Anyway, I gotta go.
Bye.</i>

37:36.755 --> 37:38.788
Wait. 24!

37:43.262 --> 37:44.694
She's beautiful, Syd.

37:44.696 --> 37:47.631
Thanks.

37:47.633 --> 37:51.468
I... I got her a soccer ball sewn
at a girls school in Kabul.

37:51.470 --> 37:53.370
It was a birthday present.

37:53.372 --> 37:55.605
Since you're going back,
can you take it to her?

37:55.607 --> 37:58.675
Sure, yeah, no,
I'd be more than happy to.

37:58.677 --> 38:00.744
Syd, I-i don't even...

38:00.746 --> 38:02.946
Drew, stop apologizing.

38:02.948 --> 38:04.381
This is what I signed up for.

38:04.383 --> 38:06.616
It may not be what Riley
signed up for,

38:06.618 --> 38:08.618
but hey, what can I do
about that?

38:08.620 --> 38:11.054
Get hammered on near beer?

38:11.056 --> 38:12.322
[ Scoffs ]

38:12.324 --> 38:13.423
I'm buying.

38:13.425 --> 38:14.991
Tempting.

38:14.993 --> 38:16.660
Rain check?

38:16.662 --> 38:20.363
Yeah, of course.

38:20.365 --> 38:21.998
Good night, major.

38:22.000 --> 38:23.800
Good night, captain.

38:24.803 --> 38:27.537
[ "I of the storm" by of
monsters and men playing ]

38:30.342 --> 38:33.076
So, the staring at Jordan
and Scott earlier.

38:33.078 --> 38:36.413
Was that wistful memories
or painful future?

38:36.415 --> 38:38.381
I don't know.

38:38.383 --> 38:39.716
After everything
we've been through,

38:39.718 --> 38:40.684
nothing's easy anymore.

38:40.686 --> 38:42.485
Never is with you two.

38:42.487 --> 38:44.621
Meantime, if I were you,
I'd start building up

38:44.623 --> 38:47.357
those chicken legs before
someone tries to barbecue them.

38:47.359 --> 38:49.592
Get some sun on 'em.
It's summertime!

38:49.594 --> 38:51.361
All right, enough talking.
Let's go, old man.

38:51.363 --> 38:52.762
Come on. Come on!

38:52.764 --> 38:56.333
Okay, that's... that's...

38:56.335 --> 38:58.034
Yeah, I'll catch up!

38:58.036 --> 38:59.703
Shannon, you don't have all
the answers, okay?

38:59.705 --> 39:00.670
You're still an intern,

39:00.672 --> 39:02.405
and you're gonna make mistakes,

39:02.407 --> 39:03.473
but it's how you learn.

39:03.475 --> 39:05.041
So, just every once in a while,

39:05.043 --> 39:08.745
maybe stop talking
and listen a little bit.

39:08.747 --> 39:10.947
Tell you what, you help me work
on my work game,

39:10.949 --> 39:13.016
and I'll help you work
on your off-duty game.

39:13.018 --> 39:15.485
I don't know. I'm just...
I'm not good at that stuff.

39:15.487 --> 39:17.053
All right? I'm not really big
on hooking up.

39:17.055 --> 39:18.955
Oh, wow, Sam's here.

39:18.957 --> 39:20.490
The station's two blocks away.

39:20.492 --> 39:21.925
They usually sit at the counter,

39:21.927 --> 39:24.361
but making mistakes
is how you learn, right?

39:24.363 --> 39:25.245
Don't call him over here.

39:25.246 --> 39:26.128
Hey!
I am gonna kill you.

39:26.131 --> 39:27.997
Jonah! Sam!
Oh, my god.

39:27.999 --> 39:30.567
Well, at least I'll have two
firemen to rescue me.

39:30.569 --> 39:31.501
[ Laughs ]

39:31.503 --> 39:32.802
Hey.

39:32.804 --> 39:34.537
Hey, guys, what's up?

39:34.539 --> 39:37.574
Uh, breakfast.
You want some company?

39:40.879 --> 39:43.012
- Yes.
- Okay.

39:43.014 --> 39:45.415
[ Sighs ]

39:45.417 --> 39:47.484
Hey.
We're gonna need another round.

39:47.486 --> 39:48.718
Yeah, we're thirsty.

39:48.720 --> 39:50.420
Can I get a shot of Tequila,
please?

39:50.422 --> 39:51.888
- Ooh!
- Four shots.

39:51.890 --> 39:53.022
Four shots of Tequila.

39:53.024 --> 39:55.058
* I feel it break my skin *

39:55.060 --> 39:57.560
- Oh. You...
- Sorry, I touched it.

39:57.562 --> 39:59.596
[ Chuckling ]
Go for it.

39:59.598 --> 40:01.498
It's Annie, right?

40:01.500 --> 40:03.533
Yeah, good memory.

40:03.535 --> 40:04.567
It's Scott.

40:04.569 --> 40:06.036
Scott, right.

40:06.037 --> 40:07.504
So that <i> was</i> you
that I saw earlier

40:07.506 --> 40:08.671
at the hospital.

40:08.673 --> 40:10.173
Yeah, you should have said hi.

40:10.175 --> 40:13.443
Next time I will.

40:15.981 --> 40:18.181
Why don't you take a few days
off and come with me?

40:18.183 --> 40:20.417
I'll show you the best
crab shack in Maryland.

40:20.419 --> 40:23.653
We can drive down to ocean city,
see Assateague island.

40:23.655 --> 40:25.188
I got my gym opening this week.

40:25.190 --> 40:27.524
I got my life savings in
that thing, you know that?

40:27.526 --> 40:29.426
Yeah, I know, it's just...

40:29.428 --> 40:32.729
We knew this was gonna be hard
if I got in.

40:32.731 --> 40:35.198
Yeah, well, a few hours ago,

40:35.200 --> 40:37.467
I thought that'd be next year,
not right now.

40:37.469 --> 40:40.570
Okay, so fly out after things
settle down with the gym.

40:40.572 --> 40:42.472
Things settle down,
I'm going belly up.

40:42.474 --> 40:44.808
I mean, it's just me doing it
all right now.

40:44.810 --> 40:46.109
Maybe you could come back.

40:46.111 --> 40:48.328
Ah, I don't know.

40:48.329 --> 40:50.546
I got to come out of the gate
strong or I'm gonna get buried.

40:50.549 --> 40:52.115
[ Chuckles ]

40:52.117 --> 40:54.584
Long-distance thing
never works out, huh?

40:54.586 --> 40:59.556
That's it, we're just gonna rip
the band-aid off, huh?

41:04.129 --> 41:09.599
* And I'm shaking like a leaf *

41:09.601 --> 41:12.936
* and they call me under *

41:12.938 --> 41:14.771
See you later, Kenny Fournette.

41:14.773 --> 41:17.507
* And I wither underneath *

41:17.509 --> 41:20.543
[ Engine starts ]

41:20.545 --> 41:24.747
* In this storm I feel it *

41:25.617 --> 41:28.618
* and they call me underneath *

41:28.620 --> 41:31.521
Goodbye, Gwen.

41:31.523 --> 41:34.023
* To the storm *

